342
00:27:30,930 --> 00:27:32,070
When I woke up in the middle of the night,

343
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,190
I found someone in my room.

344
00:27:33,470 --> 00:27:33,870
It's...

345
00:27:34,900 --> 00:27:35,680
His body,

346
00:27:35,830 --> 00:27:36,760
like I said,

347
00:27:36,950 --> 00:27:38,620
was pieced up like a puzzle.

348
00:27:38,880 --> 00:27:39,480
Then the face

349
00:27:40,340 --> 00:27:41,310
looked dead.

350
00:27:41,980 --> 00:27:42,960
He wanted me to help him.

351
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:45,400
I thought if I didn't help him,

352
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:46,390
he might hurt my mom.

353
00:27:47,190 --> 00:27:48,220
That's why I asked him to take me

354
00:27:48,220 --> 00:27:49,070
to the place he died.

355
00:27:49,310 --> 00:27:50,380
Why didn't you bring him to the police station?

356
00:27:51,610 --> 00:27:53,960
Yes, why not?

357
00:27:55,130 --> 00:27:55,660
Maybe

358
00:27:56,260 --> 00:27:56,750
Because in the comics...

359
00:27:56,750 --> 00:27:58,210
Let me repeat what you just said.

360
00:27:59,390 --> 00:28:00,360
For some reason,

361
00:28:00,360 --> 00:28:01,670
you took this person to your house.

362
00:28:02,380 --> 00:28:04,270
Whether he was alive or not,

363
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:06,630
you just dismembered him

364
00:28:06,650 --> 00:28:07,670
